  "texts": [
    "The temperature of the BSF composting is mesophilic and the aeration can be improved on the compost system by the movement and natural turning of the waste by the larvae (Sarpong et al., 2019).",
    "As suggested by Cooperband (2002), the optimum temperatures for bacterial decomposition are at 21-49 °C.",
    "While, other researchers have reported that high temperature (i.e.",
    "45 °C or more) could cut down the pathogenic loads of the final compost (Banks, 2014; Dortmans, 2015; Tirado, 2008).",
    "As temperature is one of the important factors which affect the nutrient availability (Pang et al., 2020) and optimum waste consumption by BSFL, maintaining relatively constant waste temperature (about 30 °C) is inevitable (Pang et al., 2020)."
  ],
